info.name: Scrappet Kaiser Princess
info.attribution:
An original game by Zoql available under CC BY-SA-NC 4.0. Thanks to Ly (coloring) and meBID (digital version). Adapted for use on virtualtabletop.io by LawDawg96.

For more information and additional versions of the game, see https://zoql.itch.io/scrappetkaiserprincess.
info.description: Place workers on game board and assign them tasks of earning money, buying cards, trading for cards, or dueling for cards. Play 7 rounds and earn as many points as possible. Compare against game ending point chart to see how well you did.

joker-red.label: Sour Broccoli
joker-red.text2: 3 Strength. This card can only leave your binder for duels in the Alley.

joker-blue.label: Rotten Puddle
joker-blue.text2: 1 Strength. Lose 5 Ego at the end of the round.

diamonds-a.label: Cowboy Spitball
diamonds-a.text2: -1 Strength. Only Penny may trade this card. Gain 1 less Ego at the end of the round.

diamonds-2.label: Eggbert the Resilient
diamonds-2.text2: 0 Strength. If you have 50 Ego, +9 Strength to this card

joker-black.label: Baby Filkiss
joker-black.text2: Strength 12. Lose the Ego you bet, then reduce the amount of bet Ego by half (round down) for the Strength check.

joker-red.label: Dirk Canyon, Esquire
joker-red.text2: Strength 15. Lose 1 Buck for each Ego you bet. If you cannot pay the full amount, you cannot gain this card.

joker-blue.label: Dog Bower's Dad
joker-blue.text2: Strength 5. Immediately gain the amount of Ego you bet.

diamonds-a.label: Carl
diamonds-a.text2: Strength 10. Reduce the amount of Ego bet by 10. If you tie or lose this duel, lose the card you dueled with

diamonds-2.label: Both of Griswald's Knees
diamonds-2.text2: Strength 8. If you win this duel without betting Ego, gain 10 Ego. Otherwise, lose the Ego you bet.

diamonds-3.label: Lumby But Giga
diamonds-3.text2: Strength 11. After this duel, lose 15 Ego.

joker-black.label: Rainy Day
joker-black.text2: All kids at the Playground and the Lemonade Stand return home. If Mindy is at the Alley, instead of dueling, she may buy Dues' revealed card with Bucks

joker-red.label: Intense Dodgeball
joker-red.text2: All kids at the Lemonade Stand earn double Money

joker-blue.label: Toy Sale
joker-blue.text2: If Spiff is at the Playground, Spiff loses all his held cards and bucks, and does not trade this round. Remove 1 extra card from the Playground during cleanup

diamonds-a.label: Big Sister
diamonds-a.text2: If Link is at the Store, he loses 4 Bucks before purchasing any Booster cards

diamonds-2.label: BOGO
diamonds-2.text2: If Penny is at the Lemonade Stand, she does not gain any Bucks, losing 5 instead if possible.

diamonds-3.label: Teenager Takeover
diamonds-3.text2: All kids at the store get one free Booster card.

diamonds-4.label: Dropped Wallet
diamonds-4.text2: Replace each card in the Playground with a card from the top of the Store deck. Replaced cards go to the bottom of the deck.

diamonds-5.label: First Subs!
diamonds-5.text2: All kids at the alley gain 10 Bucks

diamonds-6.label: Where's Our Cut?
diamonds-6.text2: Gain 10 Ego. If this would force you to unfriend a kid, unfriend them now.

diamonds-7.label: Bossy Bestie
diamonds-7.text2: If multiple kids are at the Lemonade Stand, no Bucks are gained

diamonds-8.label: Stray Cat Distraction
diamonds-8.text2: If multiple kids are at the Store, they lose all their Bucks and gain only 1 card

diamonds-9.label: New Video Game
diamonds-9.text2: Jessa can move to another location after activating her current location's effects, collecting any needed bucks or cards on the way. She performs her action as if Mindy were with her.

diamonds-10.label: Unexpected Holiday
diamonds-10.text2: Kids at the Lemonade Stand only gain half the Bucks they would normally have, rounded down.

joker-black.label: Are We Still Friends?
joker-black.text2: If you no longer own your Starter Card, immediately send Jessa home and Unfriend her

joker-red.label: Red Joker
joker-red.text1: Scoring: Ego + Strength + Money + 10 per friend

fields.text: This will reset the board and start a new game. Are you sure?

86w1.text: If more than 6 cards, stack in the far right holder with oldest on bottom and newest on top. Click button.
